The RAND drug policy institute is fighting a battle right now to have Gateway theory stricken from so called &quot;Drug Education&quot; because it missleads people by telling them lies. According to the government's own numbers, the amount of Americans who have tried Marijuana is 76,300,000. The amount of americans who have tried Heroin is only 2,730,000. Tell me how Marijuanna leads to harder drugs looking at those numbers. It isnt even a significant majority, not even close. The TRUTH is there is NO evidence of any such thing as &quot;Gateway Theory&quot;<br>
